description:
This is part 2/5 of an evolutionary steering behaviors coding challenge. The goal is to create a system where autonomous steering agents evolve the behavior of eating food (green dots) and avoiding poison (red dots). This challenge is part of the spring 2017 ITP "Intelligence and Learning" course.

💻Challenge: https://thecodingtrain.com/CodingChallenges/069.2-steering-evolution.html
🎥Part 1: https://youtu.be/flxOkx0yLrY
🎥Part 3: https://youtu.be/vZUWTlK7D2Q
🎥Part 4: https://youtu.be/ykOcaInciBI
🎥Part 5: https://youtu.be/VnFF5V5DS8s
